defs.docs: Abstracts over a pile of bits (basically unsigned primitives)

defs.name: bits
defs.docs: How many bits it has

defs.name: bytes
defs.docs: How many bytes it has

defs.name: from_byte
defs.docs: Convert a byte into this type (lowest-order bits set)

defs.name: count_ones
defs.docs: Count the number of 1's in the bitwise repr

defs.name: zero
defs.docs: Get `0`

defs.name: one
defs.docs: Get `1`

defs.name: BitVec
defs.docs: The bitvector type.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty `BitVec`.

defs.name: from_elem
defs.docs:
Creates a `BitVec` that holds `nbits` elements, setting each element
 to `bit`.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs: Constructs a new, empty `BitVec` with the specified capacity.

defs.name: from_bytes
defs.docs:
Transforms a byte-vector into a `BitVec`. Each byte becomes eight bits,
 with the most significant bits of each byte coming first. Each
 bit becomes `true` if equal to 1 or `false` if equal to 0.

defs.name: from_fn
defs.value: fn <F> (len: usize, mut f: F) -> Self
defs.docs:
Creates a `BitVec` of the specified length where the value at each index
 is `f(index)`.

defs.name: blocks
defs.docs: Iterator over the underlying blocks of data

defs.name: storage
defs.docs: Exposes the raw block storage of this BitVec

defs.name: storage_mut
defs.docs: Exposes the raw block storage of this BitVec

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Retrieves the value at index `i`, or `None` if the index is out of bounds.

defs.name: set
defs.value: fn (&mut self, i: usize, x: bool) -> ()
defs.docs: Sets the value of a bit at an index `i`.

defs.name: set_all
defs.docs: Sets all bits to 1.

defs.name: negate
defs.docs: Flips all bits.

defs.name: union
defs.docs:
Calculates the union of two bitvectors. This acts like the bitwise `or`
 function.

defs.name: intersect
defs.docs:
Calculates the intersection of two bitvectors. This acts like the
 bitwise `and` function.

defs.name: difference
defs.docs: Calculates the difference between two bitvectors.

defs.name: all
defs.docs: Returns `true` if all bits are 1.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the elements of the vector in order.

defs.name: none
defs.docs: Returns `true` if all bits are 0.

defs.name: any
defs.docs: Returns `true` if any bit is 1.

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs:
Organises the bits into bytes, such that the first bit in the
 `BitVec` becomes the high-order bit of the first byte. If the
 size of the `BitVec` is not a multiple of eight then trailing bits
 will be filled-in with `false`.

defs.name: eq_vec
defs.docs:
Compares a `BitVec` to a slice of `bool`s.
 Both the `BitVec` and slice must have the same length.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shortens a `BitVec`, dropping excess elements.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more bits to be inserted in the given
 `BitVec`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid frequent reallocations.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs:
Reserves the minimum capacity for exactly `additional` more bits to be inserted in the
 given `BitVec`. Does nothing if the capacity is already sufficient.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs:
Returns the capacity in bits for this bit vector. Inserting any
 element less than this amount will not trigger a resizing.

defs.name: grow
defs.value: fn (&mut self, n: usize, value: bool) -> ()
defs.docs: Grows the `BitVec` in-place, adding `n` copies of `value` to the `BitVec`.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Removes the last bit from the BitVec, and returns it. Returns None if the BitVec is empty.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Pushes a `bool` onto the end.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the total number of bits in this vector

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Sets the number of bits that this BitVec considers initialized.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if there are no bits in this vector

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears all bits in this vector.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs:
Shrinks the capacity of the underlying storage as much as
 possible.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator for `BitVec`.

defs.name: Blocks
defs.docs: An iterator over the blocks of a `BitVec`.
